Schools in Kenya have finally been opened today (January 4, 2021), after a lockdown of nine months as a result of Coronavirus pandemic. However, it was not clear when private schools in the country will re-open as a result of economic devastations caused by the virus, forcing parents to relocate their children to the public schools. Close analysis showed a picture of a rush by parents seeking places in the public schools, which are not enough to accommodate all given the high and sudden demand.